# Real World Scenario

## Situation

A Linux administrator needs to identify whether the SSH service is running.

Instead of reviewing hundreds of processes manually:

```bash
ps aux | grep ssh
```

The administrator quickly identifies the required process.

This reduces troubleshooting time significantly.

---

# Help Desk Ticket

## Issue

Employee reports:

"I can access websites by IP address but not by website name."

### Investigation

Verified:

```bash
ping 8.8.8.8
```

Successful.

Verified:

```bash
ping google.com
```

Failed.

### Root Cause

DNS resolution failure.

### Resolution

Reviewed:

```bash
cat /etc/resolv.conf
```

Corrected DNS configuration.

Issue resolved.

